        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Rochester</placeName>
                <date>May 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1868</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Wm. B. Hackenberg. Esq</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I have received<lb/> last <date>Friday</date>, your note dated
                    <date>April 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi></date>,<lb/> in which you inform me, that, I
                owe<lb/> for Subscription to the Occident, twenty-<lb/>two (22) dollars.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I consider in my duty,<lb/> out of respect to you, and the
                other<lb/> Executors of the late <persName>Rev Mr Leeser</persName>;<lb/> to state
                to you, that, this charge is<lb/> entirely mistaken, and I am highly<lb/>
                <sic>suprised</sic> at this demand.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">About nineteen years<lb/> ago, when I was Rabbi of
                    <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>,<lb/>
                <persName>Rev. Mr Leeser</persName> paid me a visit; we</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>became acquainted and befriended;<lb/> and he offered to send me <hi rend="underline"
                    >gratu</hi>-<lb/><hi rend="underline">ously</hi>, his periodical; and
                requested<lb/> me to send him, now and then, some<lb/> article, which I did.
                During<lb/> this whole time, I never was asked<lb/> for any pay, and never did
                pay<lb/> anything; for otherwise my limited<lb/> income, would not have allowed<lb/>
                me, to be a subscriber.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">When I read the sad<lb/> news, that my good, old friend, was<lb/>
                taken from this life, and his periodical<lb/> shall be continued by <persName>Mr
                    Sulzberger</persName>,<lb/> I thought, first to inform that<lb/> gentleman to
                discontinue the sending<lb/> of it; as I have not the pleasure of<lb/> being
                acquainted with him, and of</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>course, cannot expect of him, to send<lb/> me as his predecessor did
                    <sic>gratuously</sic>;<lb/> but after mature reflection, I thought<lb/> this
                might be considered as an<lb/>
                <sic>offence</sic>, against the successor; but<lb/> under no consideration, would
                my<lb/> pecuniary circumstances allow me,<lb/> to pay for all the Jewish
                papers,<lb/> which are sent to me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I hope this explanation<lb/> will satisfy you and your
                colleagues.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Most Respectfully &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">A. Guinzburg</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">per <persName>Tillie Guinzburg</persName></p>
            <p rend="The following is added in pencil in a different handwriting.">all right<lb/>
                <persName>MBH</persName></p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">Guinzberg</persName></hi> was a<lb/>
                dead head</p>
        </body>
